review_blob: Big white head..good aroma.. choco, coffee, licorice, caramel taste.. slight bitter after taste. Above average black ipa
Medium head, yellowish and light hazy. Firstly bitter, hoppy and tasty, intense and pleasant on the palate, citrus traces. Really enjoyable IPA.
Good beer overall..small white head and orange body, smells sweety and bready, taste of toasted malt and grain, nice smoky flavour and sligtly bitter first and aftertaste..will have another one :)
